    "as well as students' over reliance on AI which negatively affects their critical thinking and problem solving skills [27] as well as hallucinative misinformation and a lack of reliability [32].",
    "ChatGPT in higher education settingsWhile educators hold divergent views about ChatGPT [56], a number of researchers have attempted to address the perspective of students [9,44], teachers [10,26] and the management educators [30,35] when adopting ChatGPT in higher educational settings.",
    "Others have designed the educational framework for generative AI in education such as AI Ecological Education Policy Framework [8] and the IDEE Theoretical Framework [45].Several studies [27,38,50] also identified that there is an obvious gap in the literature regarding the real-world application and implications of ChatGPT in higher education.",
    "As the ChatGPT is the game changer for education [13] and since its inevitable banning is likely to result in students wanting access more due to increased attention and psychological reactivity [30], this will likely drive students to want access more.",
    "Therefore it is paramount for universities to adapt and embrace it in a way that supports students' learning and prepares them for the challenges in the AI-era future [46]."
